article.headline: Seton Hall 83, Morgan St. 63
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Eugene Harvey scored 20 points to lead Seton Hall to an 83-63 victory over Morgan State on Saturday. Harvey hit 7-of-8 from the floor. He made six of his free-throw attempts as the Pirates (2-1) shot 20-of-30 from the line. Grant Billmeier contributed 14 points for Seton Hall, and Brian Laing added another 13 points and grabbed 12 rebounds. Ronald Timus led Morgan State (0-4) with 22 points and six rebounds. He shot 7-of-13 and 7-of-8 from the line and the Bears shot 17-of-21 from the line. Reggie Holmes added 12 points for the Bears. Timothy Berkley contributed another eight points and grabbed six more rebounds. Seton Hall led Morgan State 41-20 at the half. Morgan narrowed the gap in the second half, but it wasn't enough for the win.
